Trophy ceremony during the Carling Currie Cup 2022 Final between the Griquas and Pumas held at Windhoek Draught Park in Kimberley. Charle Lombard/BackpagePix KIMBERLY - The Pumas created history on Saturday by clinching their first-ever Currie Cup trophy to beat Griquas 26-19 on their home patch in Kimberley. Jimmy Stonehouse’s men became only the eighth union to win the Currie Cup. READ: Griquas stun Bulls to reach Currie Cup final The Pumas were immense in defense and sealed victory with three tries to one.